The paper focuses on using formal methods to explore chemical reaction networks, which falls under the category of systems and synthetic biology. Therefore, cs.SY is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses using Alloy, a tool for expressing structural constraints and behavior in software systems, which could fall under cs.CE (computational engineering, finance, and science). The exploration of CRNs with desired functionality could also fall under cs.AI (artificial intelligence) and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses using CRNs for analog function computation, which could fall under cs.LG (machine learning).
